1 sachet Classic Roast Seasoning
2 Garlic
1 Ciabatta
1 Celery
300 g Diced Chicken
1 packet Flaked Almonds
1 packet Garlic Aioli
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 Tomato
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 drizzle olive oil

• Roughly chop tomato. Thinly slice celery. Finely
chop garlic.
• Cut or tear ciabatta into bite-sized chunks.
• In a medium bowl, combine diced chicken, classic roast seasoning, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat.
Toast flaked almonds until golden, 2-3 minutes.
Transfer to a bowl and set aside.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a
generous drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook ciabatta until golden and slightly crispy,
4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
Season to taste. Transfer to a large bowl.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a
drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes.
TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it’s no longer
pink inside.

• To the bowl with croutons, add mixed salad leaves, tomato, celery and a drizzle of balsamic vinegar and olive oil. Toss to combine and season to taste.
Little cooks: Take the lead by tossing the salad!

• Divide crouton salad between bowls. Top with
chicken. Drizzle over garlic aioli.
• Sprinkle with toasted almonds to serve. Enjoy!
Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling
over the toasted almonds!